# Workflow — sessions, files, and agent routing

Work in this repo **builds into files**, not chat history. A session that doesn't update the files below didn't happen (three ad-hoc sessions skipped this and PLAN.md drifted a month stale — see [051](mdc:docs/decisions/051-product-review.md)).

## Session types

| Type | Where | Rules |
|---|---|---|
| Tracked build session | **New chat**, paste the AGENTS.md session template | Full acceptance checklist + end-of-session gate |
| Ad-hoc fix / polish (< ~1 hr) | Existing or new chat | **Still runs the end-of-session gate** — ad-hoc is not exempt |
| Review / audit | New chat, read-only tools | Must end as decisions + session prompts, not just a report (see below) |

## End-of-session gate (every session, including ad-hoc)

1. `docs/decisions/NNN-<slug>.md` filed — take the **next free number** (`ls docs/decisions/ | sort`; collision index in [docs/decisions/README.md](mdc:docs/decisions/README.md))
2. **PLAN.md refreshed** — last-updated line, Recent decisions, Next up
3. AGENTS.md inventory + [components.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/components.mdc) updated if helpers/components were added
4. `npm run check` + `npm run test` pass (note the date in PLAN.md › Repo gate). Prefer waiting for GitHub Actions **CI** green on `main` before assuming Vercel will succeed — CI now also runs `npm run build` (same compile path as Vercel).
5. **Provide a copy-paste commit message** for the session's changes (scoped to this session's files if the working tree mixes sessions), then **explicitly confirm we're good to close out** — Parker commits/pushes himself unless he explicitly asks the agent to commit/push.

## Git / ship (solo — read before opening a PR)

`main` is protected: required status check **`check-and-test`**, no force-push. **Admin bypass is on** (Include administrators / “Do not allow bypassing…” is **unchecked**) so Parker can push straight to `main` without a PR ([106](mdc:docs/decisions/106-main-admin-bypass.md)). **Reviews are not required.** Required checks still stop casual/non-admin broken landings ([097](mdc:docs/decisions/097-vercel-deploy-ci-build-gate.md), [105](mdc:docs/decisions/105-solo-git-ship-agent-guidance.md)). This is **not** a mandate to run every change through a pull request.

| Do | Don't |
|---|---|
| Prefer working on **`main`** for solo sessions when the tree is clean | Invent a PR solely because `main` is protected |
| End with a **copy-paste commit message**; when Parker asks to commit/push, **push to `main`** (admin bypass) | Reuse an open feature branch / PR for **unrelated** work from another chat |
| Open a PR only when Parker asks, or if a push is blocked for a non-bypass path | `git reset --hard` / rewrite history to “fix” a push without checking for other WIP |
| Keep local `npm run check` (+ `test` / `build` when touching ship paths) before pushing to `main` | Treat Cursor’s commit-and-push “current branch” as permission to pile onto someone else’s PR |

**Why this exists:** An agent once opened PR #1 after hitting protection; later chats stacked onto the same branch. Admins-enforced made every land a PR (#2–#3); owner turned that off for solo friction ([106](mdc:docs/decisions/106-main-admin-bypass.md)).

## Task-to-agent routing

| Task | Route to |
|---|---|
| Repo-wide audit, multi-area exploration | **Parallel read-only explore subagents**, one per concern (security / UX / docs each got one in 051) |
| Diff > 400 LOC before push (any module, not just library) | **Read-only review subagent (Bugbot)** — mobile + RLS + citation regressions |
| Diffs touching RLS, Edge Functions, auth, storage policies | **Security-review subagent** before push |
| Structured findings, quantitative analyses, audits | **Canvas** beside the chat; the durable outcome still goes in `docs/decisions/` |
| Ambiguous scope, multiple valid architectures | **Plan mode** first; lock Phase-0 structure before building (module-kickoff.mdc) |
| Independent parallel workstreams | **Background agents**, one per workstream — never interleave two workstreams in one chat |
| "What's the current state?" questions | Answer from **PLAN.md + latest 3 decision files** before searching code |

## Decision-first reviews

A review or analysis is unfinished until it becomes:

1. **Locked decisions** — put open calls to Parker as explicit multiple-choice questions, record the answers
2. **Session prompts** — copy-paste-ready prompts appended to PLAN.md › Session prompts
3. **A decision-log entry** — findings that don't change PLAN.md will go stale and be lost
